Cell.Text: The Augur? Really? Well, it's certainly not my place to say anything about it. | I think you'd better go see Mirabelle Ervine.
What? The Augur? Oh no, I'm quite sure that's... He's nothing I'm involved in. No, no. | Mirabelle Ervine... Or Tolfdir. They're qualified to discuss him. Not me, definitely not.
It's not enough that you've stolen the spotlight with this Eye thing, now you're looking for the Augur? | I'm not sure what you're playing at, but you'd do well to remember your place around here.

The Augur? Tragic story, really. At least, the way I heard it. But that was a long time ago. | It was some experiment gone horribly wrong. Ghastly results, I was told. And his ghost still roams the halls, they say. | Of course, on further reflection, that may have simply been an attempt to scare me. Hmm. | Perhaps I'll ask Tolfdir what really happened. I understand he was here at the time.
Oh, no. No, that won't do at all. | Not my problem. Not even a little. Take it to Tolfdir, he's supposed to be looking after you lot.
[S] That's nothing you need to concern yourself with.
The what of what? No. No idea. | If it's important, maybe Tolfdir knows. He seems to know a lot.
Huh? That sounds ominous. Are you getting yourself into even more trouble? | Did you ask Mirabelle? She runs things around here, after all.
I've never heard of anything like that. Did you ask Tolfdir? He's been here a long time, and seems to know almost everything.
What? I have no idea what you're talking about.

Well now, there's a name I haven't heard in some time. | My goodness, it's been years since I've spoken with him. I suppose he's still down in the Midden, but I haven't checked. | Are you going to see him? Do tell him 'hello' for me, won't you?

Node.Caption: MG04Stage40AugurQuestionBranchTopic: Have you ever heard of the Augur of Dunlain?

Cell.Text: I am that which you have been seeking. | Your efforts are in vain. It has already begun. | But those who have sent you have not told you what they seek. What you seek.

Node.Caption: MG04Stage40AugurBranchTopic: So you're the Augur of Dunlain?

Cell.Text: His questions were answered. He now possesses the ability to tap into that source of great knowledge. | The details are inconsequential. Your current existence will end at the completion of his ritual. | Like those before him, warnings to your Arch-Mage went unheeded.

Node.Caption: MG04Stage40AugurFollowUp: What did you tell the Arch-Mage?

Cell.Text: Your Arch-Mage insisted on knowing the origins of this power. He believed it Divine. | Were he to survive, he would find his perception affirmed.

Node.Caption: MG04Stage40AugurFollowUp1: What's this ritual supposed to do?

Cell.Text: [S] That which should be done was never questioned, only that which can be done. | More discreet inquiries would be required for that to be clarified. | Take your own piece of knowledge and go: your Arch-Mage cannot proceed if disaster is to be avoided.

Node.Caption: MG04Stage40AugurFollowUp2: Didn't you tell him it's dangerous?

Cell.Text: S|I'm not sure what just happened but I assure you I will get to the bottom of it.
Whatever it is those Psijics are up to. They cannot be trusted. | For all we know, he's here to scout out the College. I'm sure they want to undermine our efforts.

Node.Caption: MG04Stage40AncanoGreetFollowUp: Get to the bottom of what?

Cell.Text: This! This... Orb. The Eye of Magnus, whatever you want to call it. It's clearly powerful, and no doubt they want it for themselves! | I expect to be informed if they make any future attempts to contact you.

Node.Caption: MG04Stage40AncanoGreetFollowup2: What efforts would they be undermining?

Cell.Text: The artifact recovered in Saarthal, dormant, waiting. It is knowledge, and it is power. | Your Arch-Mage, and those for whom he entreats, would exploit this knowledge.

Node.Caption: MG04Stage40AugurFollowUpB: Why did the Arch-Mage come to see you?

Cell.Text: Underneath the College. It's not the nicest place, so if you go down there, please do be careful.

Very well. It's not something often discussed, as it might be... misunderstood by the locals. | The Augur is down in the Midden, below the College. I don't recommend going down there unless it's absolutely necessary.
I think perhaps there are more important things to be focused on.

Node.Caption: MG04MirabelleAugurInfoBranchTopic: (Favor) Can you please help me find this Augur?

Cell.Text: Indeed. And so you have come looking, though you do not know why. | Like others before you, you blindly follow a path to your own destruction. | The Thalmor came seeking answers as well, unaware they will be his undoing. | Your path now follows his, though you will arrive too late.

Node.Caption: MG04Stage40AugurResponse1: I was told to find you.

Cell.Text: You seek that which all who wield magic seek. Knowledge. | You shall find this: Knowledge will corrupt. It will destroy. It will consume. | You seek meaning, shelter in Knowledge. You will not find it. | The Thalmor sought the same thing, and it shall lead to his end as it has so many others.

Node.Caption: MG04Stage40AugurResponse2: And what is it I'm seeking?

Cell.Text: He sought me as well. To gain knowledge of that which has been brought to your College. | He did not see the peril in knowing, but he shall see it soon enough, as shall you all.

Node.Caption: MG04Stage40AugurArchMageInitial1: What does the Arch-Mage have to do with this?

Cell.Text: Time has little meaning. Events occur simultaneously, branching out into infinite possibilities before collapsing. | To place one such event in a linear sequence is... taxing. By your perception, it has already happened, though recently.
The one who calls himself Ancano. | He seeks information about the Eye, just as you do. | His path will cross yours in time, but first you must find that which you need.

No, though you may be the last. The one who calls himself Ancano has sought my knowledge as well, through very different questions. | Your path differs from most. You are being guided, pushed towards something. | It is a good path, one untraveled by many. It is a path that will save your College. I will tell you what you need to know to follow it further.

Node.Caption: MG04Stage40AugurThalmor2: I'm not the first to come see you?

Cell.Text: [S] G|You, and those aiding you, wish to know more about the Eye of Magnus. You wish to avoid the disaster of which you are not yet aware. | To see through Magnus' Eye without being blinded, you require his staff. | Events now spiral quickly towards the inevitable center, so you must act quickly. Take this knowledge to your superiors.
